  "prompt": "Are there legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering?",
  "response": "Many countries have laws requiring financial institutions to report suspicious transactions that may indicate money laundering. Specific reporting requirements vary, but generally include:\n\n1. Mandatory reporting to financial intelligence units\n2. Filing suspicious activity reports (SARs)\n3. Conducting customer due diligence\n4. Maintaining transaction records\n5. Training staff to identify potential money laundering indicators\n\nThe exact details depend on the specific jurisdiction and financial regulations.",
